            On the last point, I do not know whether I speak for the noble Lord, Lord Higgins, as well, but I should be happy to have a look at the speech to see whether we want it read into the record. If the Minister is happy to do that, that would save time.</p><p>
            On the more fundamental point and the important and helpful announcement that the Minister has just made, which will be followed with great interest by many people in the country, many of whom have been writing to us, I press her on the exact timing on the winding-up of schemes. As I heard her say it, the timetable for the PPF is that schemes will be eligible where winding-up of the scheme takes place&#x2014;I think those were her words&#x2014;after 6 April, 2005. Could she clarify further what "takes place" means, because winding-up involves quite a process. Exactly what does that mean?</p><p>
